sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant SDK as Python SDK<br/>kubeflow-training
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Validation Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant Controller as Training Operator<br/>Controller
    participant Scheduler as Scheduler<br/>(optional: Volcano)
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant MasterPod as Master Pod<br/>23456/TCP
    participant WorkerPod as Worker Pod<br/>23456/TCP
    participant Storage as S3/Object Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,Storage: Flow 1: Training Job Creation and Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f pytorchjob.yaml<br/>Auth: User credentials
    activate K8sAPI

    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>mTLS client cert
    activate Webhook
    Webhook->>Webhook: Validate replica counts,<br/>resource requests, spec
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation response (Allow/Deny)
    deactivate Webhook

    K8sAPI-->>User: PyTorchJob created
    deactivate K8sAPI

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch PyTorchJob CRD<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    activate Controller
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: PyTorchJob event

    alt Gang Scheduling Enabled
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create PodGroup<br/>ServiceAccount Token
        Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Watch PodGroups
        K8sAPI-->>Scheduler: PodGroup event
    end

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Pods (Master + Workers)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ClusterIP Services<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    MasterPod->>Registry: Pull training image<br/>Image Pull Secret
    Registry-->>MasterPod: Container image

    WorkerPod->>Registry: Pull training image<br/>Image Pull Secret
    Registry-->>WorkerPod: Container image

    WorkerPod->>Storage: Download dataset<br/>S3 credentials
    Storage-->>WorkerPod: Training data

    WorkerPod->>MasterPod: TCP connection 23456<br/>Framework coordination
    activate MasterPod
    MasterPod->>WorkerPod: Distribute training params

    loop Training Iterations
        WorkerPod->>WorkerPod: Compute gradients
        WorkerPod->>MasterPod: Send gradients
        MasterPod->>MasterPod: Aggregate gradients
        MasterPod->>WorkerPod: Send updated weights
    end

    MasterPod->>Storage: Save model checkpoint<br/>S3 credentials
    Storage-->>MasterPod: Checkpoint saved
    deactivate MasterPod

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller-->>Controller: Job marked Succeeded
    deactivate Controller

    Note over User,Storage: Flow 2: Monitoring and Observability

    participant Prometheus as Prometheus

    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>Port 8080/TCP HTTP
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Operator metrics<br/>(reconciliation time, errors)

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl get pytorchjob<br/>User credentials
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job status (Running/Succeeded/Failed)

    Note over User,Storage: Flow 3: Elastic Training (PyTorch)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create HorizontalPodAutoscaler<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Monitor worker CPU/memory
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Scale workers (2→4)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create additional worker pods
    WorkerPod->>MasterPod: New workers join training
    MasterPod->>WorkerPod: Redistribute workload
